  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/88914388" />
    <a title="Brian" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1537840-brian"><img alt="Brian" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1227048499p2/1537840.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/88914388?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brian" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brian" href="/user/show/1537840-brian">Brian</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781556593109" href="/book/show/6654181-the-shadow-of-sirius">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer88914388" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6453348718079148933">This was my second volume of Merwin&apos;s work. Ever since viewing one of those PBS short programs on poets, and listening to a critic who was in love with Merwin&apos;s poetry, I&apos;ve been trying to find that connection. It&apos;s a Pulitzer winner, yet I&apos;m still finding myself less than fully engaged. Still, there were a couple that did work for me, like &quot;Day without a name&quot;:<br/>&quot;... another light that does not/appear to be moving/ fills the horizon/ there the word/ waited for/ like a wild creature/ not glimpsed </span>
  <span id="freeText6453348718079148933" style="display:none">This was my second volume of Merwin's work. Ever since viewing one of those PBS short programs on poets, and listening to a critic who was in love with Merwin's poetry, I've been trying to find that connection. It's a Pulitzer winner, yet I'm still finding myself less than fully engaged. Still, there were a couple that did work for me, like "Day without a name":<br />"... another light that does not/appear to be moving/ fills the horizon/ there the word/ waited for/ like a wild creature/ not glimpsed this season/ not seen by anyone/ must be watching."</span>
  <a data-text-id="6453348718079148933" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
