<div id="review_349896645" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/349896645" />
    <a title="Coffy Smith" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8500371-coffy-smith"><img alt="Coffy Smith" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/349896645?book_show_action=true">Jun 16, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Coffy Smith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Coffy Smith" href="/user/show/8500371-coffy-smith">Coffy Smith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer349896645" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer805178537739167942">I know, it seems sacrilegious, but I think this book was awful. I am generally a fan of Mr. Merwin, but this book felt like he just collected a mass of broken phrases from his journal and published it all as if it were a book of poetry. There are about three really good poems here - too bad I had to read all the rest of this book to find them.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

